# Copy this file to `.env.local` and paste your Power Automate HTTP trigger URL.
#
# The flow should use a "When an HTTP request is received" trigger that accepts a
# JSON body of { "referenceNumber": "LN-..." } and responds with:
#   { referenceNumber, applicantName, status, officerComments, timeline: [{ step, status }] }
#
# NOTE: HTTP-triggered flows are not CORS-enabled by default, so a browser fetch
# may be blocked. If you hit a CORS error, front the flow with an API Management /
# Azure Function proxy that returns Access-Control-Allow-Origin, or call it via a
# Power Apps custom connector instead.
VITE_LOAN_TIMELINE_FLOW_URL=
